column2: BWWalkthrough is a class to build custom walkthroughs for your iOS App

column5: Fix autolayout with Safe Area references.
Minor UI fixes in the example project.
Bump to swift 4.2. Fix minor issues. [Closes #119]

Merge pull request #109 from kumapo/swift-4.0

Fix compile error when built with Swift 4.0 and CocoaPods
Add `@objc` to BWWalkthroughViewController.pageControlDidTouch() to fix swift 4.0 compile error

Use parent-child relationship

By calling the `addChildViewController` and `didMove(toParentViewController:)` methods, embedded child view controller can do things like presenting a modal view controller.

Merge pull request #80 from apiejh/master

Supporting size transitions

Fixed transitioning to new size

When in the middle of walkthrough, the offset would be off once the user transitions to a new size. This fixes this by going to the currentPage once the new size has been accepted.

Layout constraints fix for scrollview

Fixed constraints of scrollview subviews so that they adapt to the size of the screen when switching between landscape and portrait orientation
Add information about CocoaPod + swift 3 issue (#77)

Fixes #1

Marked BWWalkthroughPageViewController properties as IBInspectable.

Note: IB doesn't correctly support CGPoint of CGFloat. So if you modify speed or speedVariance via "IBInspectable" in IB you can only use Integer values. To set CGFloat value update directly the Runtime Attributes panel as you did before this commit.
